<div class="container">
    <div class="row g-5 mb-5">
        <%= image_tag 'weatherai-main-photo.png', alt: "Weather AI main appearance", width: '100%' %>
    </div>
    <div class="row g-5">
        <div class="col-6">
            <%= image_tag 'weatherai-2.png', alt: 'weatherai tablet format', width: "100%" %>
        </div>
        <div class="col-6">
            <div class='px-2'>
                <h3>Overview</h3>
                <p>
                    Weather AI is a global weather app built with React, integrating the ChatGPT API and OpenWeather API. It provides real-time weather updates, sunrise and sunset times, and wind conditions.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="my-5 px-2">
            <h3>Challenges & Solutions</h3>
                <div>
                    <p><strong>Prompt Construction:</strong> - Crafting effective prompts was tricky. Solved by iterating, testing, and researching best practices.</p>
                    <p><strong>Learning React</strong> - Managing state and API calls was challenging. Overcame it by investigating hooks (useState, useEffect) and component structure.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="my-5 px-2">
                <h3>Responsabilities</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>Learning & Experimentation</strong> - Explored a new front-end tool while refining development skills.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Creative Design</strong> - Had fun crafting a clean, modern interface.
                </p>
            </div>
            <%= image_tag 'weatherai-1.png', alt: 'weatherai tablet format', width: "100%" %>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>